@startuml fig-dns-docker-topology
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title Docker Compose DNS Topology — Seminar 10 Part 2

package "Docker Compose Network" as net #F5F5F5 {

    component "web\npython:3\nhttp.server :8000" as web #C8E6C9

    component "dns-server\nPython + dnslib\nUDP :5353" as dns #E1BEE7

    component "debug\nbusybox\n(interactive shell)" as debug #FFE0B2

    cloud "Docker Embedded\nDNS Resolver\n127.0.0.11" as ddns #ECEFF1
}

debug -[#1565C0]down-> ddns : dig web\n(service name)
ddns -[#43A047]down-> web : resolves to\ncontainer IP

debug -[#1565C0]-> dns : dig @dns-server\nmyservice.lab.local
dns -[#43A047]-> debug : A 10.10.10.10

note right of dns
  Custom DNS answers only
  myservice.lab.local with
  a fixed IP (10.10.10.10).
end note

legend bottom
  Docker's embedded DNS resolves service names
  automatically within the Compose network.
  The custom Python DNS server demonstrates
  how a DNS query and response work over UDP.
endlegend
@enduml
